original: Engvall, Eskil Robert, kyrkoherde. Ljung, f. 24/7/98 i Grönahög, Älvsb. 1., av hemm:äg. Claes Johan E. o. Augusta Johanna Johansson. G. 30 m. folksk:lär. Maja Wikholm. Barn: Sven Eskil f. 33, Gunnel Maria 45. — Stud:ex. i Lund 22, teol. fil. ex. 24, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Skara stift 28. Tjg. s. v. pastor i Gökhem samt s. kommin. i Hassle, kyrkoh. i S. Björke 44, tilltr. 45.
translated: Engvall, Eskil Robert, priest. Born on July 24, 1898 in Grönahög, Älvsborgs län, son of the home owner Claes Johan E. and Augusta Johanna Johansson. Married on September 30, 1930 to Maja Wikholm, who was a primary school teacher. They had two children: Sven Eskil, born in 1933, and Gunnel Maria, born in 1945. Engvall graduated from Lund University with a baccalaureate in 1922, a degree in theology in 1924, and a practical theology degree as well as ordination in Skara diocese in 1928. He served as a vicar in Gökhem and later as an assistant vicar in Hassle. He became a priest in S. Björke in 1944 and took up the post in 1945.
